Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi will pay an official visit to Tajikistan, Kyrgyzstan, Azerbaijan, Georgia and Armenia from May 20 to 27, a Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesperson announced at a press briefing Friday. Wang is visiting at the invitation of Tajikistan's FM Mukhriddin, Kyrgyzstan's FM Aidarbekov, Azerbaijan's FM Mammadyarov, Georgia's FM Zalkaliani and Armenia's FM Mnatsakanyan. He will also attend the meeting of the Shanghai Cooperation Organization Council of Foreign Ministers to be held in Kyrgyzstan, according to spokesperson Lu Kang. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Actress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame starUnrealistic expectations thwart Chinese job recruitersDelegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los Angeles